51.3	Adobe_Integrated_Runtime	Adobe AIR	Adobe Integrated Runtime, also known as Adobe AIR, is a cross-platform runtime environment developed by Adobe Systems for building Rich Internet Applications (RIA) using Adobe Flash, Adobe Flex, HTML, and Ajax, that can be run as desktop applications or on mobile devices. The runtime supports installable applications on Windows, Linux, Mac OS and some mobile operating systems such as BlackBerry Tablet OS, iOS and Android.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/64/Adobe_HQ.jpg/200px-Adobe_HQ.jpg
